$ WebGL: accessing source code from javascript

First, the source code is defined within a → development/web/HTML/tags/script[`<script>`] tag whose type is explicitly not set to `text/javascript`:
code {
<script id="fragment-shader-src" type="x-shader/x-fragment">
    varying lowp vec4 vColor;
    
    void main(void) {
      gl_FragColor = vColor;
    }
</script>
code }

Then the source code is loaded with
code {
var src_text = document.getElementById('fragment-shader-src').text;
code }

Alternatively, the source code can also be stored in so called → development/languages/JavaScript/language/expressions/primary-expressions/template-literals#js-multi-line-string[multi line strings].

sa:
  → development/web/WebGL/GLSL
